<ns3211:section xmlns:ns3211="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2se.security.messageIntegrity.messageIntegrity">
    
    <ns3212:title xmlns:ns3212="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Message Integrity</ns3212:title>
<ns3213:para xmlns:ns3213="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
Message integrity aims to provide the message recipient with a
means to verify that the message he/she/it receives is the
message which was sent, <ns3214:abbrev xmlns:ns3214="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">i.e.</ns3214:abbrev> that 
<ns3215:itemizedlist xmlns:ns3215="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
  <ns3216:listitem xmlns:ns3216="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3217:para xmlns:ns3217="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">It has not been intercepted and modified by a third party,
        the middle man.</ns3217:para></ns3216:listitem>
  <ns3218:listitem xmlns:ns3218="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3219:para xmlns:ns3219="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">It has not been accidentally corrupted due to problems
        with the communication channel.</ns3219:para></ns3218:listitem>
</ns3215:itemizedlist>
</ns3213:para>
<ns3220:para xmlns:ns3220="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">It is based on a hashing function which yields a value (a 
hash value or fingerprint)
for a message. It should be easy to calculate the fingerprint
of a message, but it should be difficult to create another
message which yields the same fingerprint.</ns3220:para>
    
